The Penn State mens indoor track team has one more tuneup before the Big Ten Championships PERIOD At  a.m PERIOD tomorrow the Nittany Lions travel to Cornell site of the Robert Kane Invitational PERIOD

A handful of Penn State athletes will travel to Ithaca N.Y. to build off a recent win against Princeton and strong performances in last weekends Nittany Lion Qualifier PERIOD

Penn State mens indoor track coach Harry Groves said that while the whole squad will not be there he expects solid results from those who compete PERIOD

 Groves said PERIOD

At the Nittany Lion Qualifier Penn State sophomore Ryan Olkowski continued his hot streak winning the long jump with a bound of   earning him a provisional spot at the NCAA Championships PERIOD

Teammate Dan Diaz threw the shot   for a firstplace finish Penn States 4x800meter relay team also came in first and Lions sophomore Ryan Blood won the pentathlon earning  points PERIOD

Penn State freshman Guy Rose ran his fastest time of the season at the Nittany Lion Qualifier to finish in second place in the 60meter high hurdles PERIOD He is anticipating Saturdays invitational to be a good chance to secure an NCAAqualifying time PERIOD

 he said PERIOD 

The 4x400meter relay team consisting of Munya Maraire Duane Reeves Steve Janci and Ben Karcz finished second with a time of . pERIOD However the time was good enough to break the Penn State record by more than two seconds PERIOD

The distance medley relay team consisting of Steve Walsh Brian Derby Ian Hahn Bradd DelMuto also secured a firstplace finish with a time of . pERIOD

The Penn State foursome had little competition in the race though PERIOD Finishing more than two seconds in front of secondplace Virginia and crushing thirdplace West Virginia by more than seven seconds the squad failed to qualify for the NCAA Championships PERIOD

After this weekends meet the Nittany Lions will embark on a voyage to Bloomington Ind. for the Big Ten Mens Indoor Track Championships Feb PERIOD  and  PERIOD Preparing for that weekend is simple Groves said PERIOD
